video.title: Big Mouth
video.synopsis: Teenage friends find their lives upended by the wonders and horrors of puberty in this edgy comedy from real-life pals Nick Kroll and Andrew Goldberg.

episodes.synopsis: As Andrew falls under the spell of the randy Hormone Monster, his buddy Nick becomes obsessed with the lack of changes in his own body.
episodes.title: Ejaculation

episodes.synopsis: A field trip goes from awkward to mortifying as Jessi navigates the demands of coupledom and gets her first period -- inside the Statue of Liberty.
episodes.title: Everybody Bleeds

episodes.synopsis: A trailer for a new movie starring The Rock leaves Andrew questioning his sexuality. Jessi and Nick's budding romance turns ugly fast.
episodes.title: Am I Gay?

episodes.synopsis: While the boys head to Jay's for a testosterone-fueled sleepover, Jessi throws a party of her own and gets caught up in mean-girl drama.
episodes.title: Sleepover: A Harrowing Ordeal of Emotional Brutality

episodes.synopsis: A steamy novel making the rounds at school inspires Jessi to explore her own sexuality -- and leaves the boys totally confused about what girls want.
episodes.title: Girls Are Horny Too

episodes.synopsis: Nick drags Andrew into the city to visit an old camp crush, but the day doesn't go as planned. Jay embarks on an emotional journey with his pillow.
episodes.title: Pillow Talk

episodes.synopsis: Andrew struggles to keep the Hormone Monster in check as he works with Missy on a science fair project. Jessi and Matthew have fun at Jay's expense.
episodes.title: Requiem for a Wet Dream

episodes.synopsis: When Leah hosts a party for the high school drama crowd, Nick wrestles with a romantic dilemma, and Andrew and Missy witness a disturbing scene.
episodes.title: The Head Push

episodes.synopsis: Family blowups, secret liaisons and an unflattering dress make Jessi's bat mitzvah a night to remember.
episodes.title: I Survived Jessi's Bat Mitzvah

episodes.synopsis: Andrew tries to drown his sorrows in a sea of porn, only to become hopelessly addicted. Coach Steve becomes a suspect in a murder spree.
episodes.title: The Pornscape

episodes.synopsis: Andrew struggles to blend in after a growth spurt, Nick worries his hormones are out of whack, and Jessi and Jay get a taste of the teen runaway life.
episodes.title: Am I Normal?

episodes.synopsis: A classmate's booming bosom sends the boys into a rapture -- and leaves the girls with a raging case of insecurity. Coach Steve drops a bombshell.
episodes.title: What Is It About Boobs?

episodes.synopsis: As Nick tries to figure out whether he has a shot with Gina, a mortifying encounter with Leah sends Andrew into a spiral of shame.
episodes.title: The Shame Wizard

episodes.synopsis: Coach Steve finally gets his chance to do sex on a lady, Nick and Andrew go on a double date, and Jessi's rebellious streak leads to big trouble.
episodes.title: Steve the Virgin

episodes.synopsis: An argument in sex ed class turns into a skit-tastic journey through the worlds of Planned Parenthood, contraceptives and STDs.
episodes.title: The Planned Parenthood Show

episodes.synopsis: Jessi and Nick dip into her dad's stash of edibles, with mind-bending results. Andrew searches for the right moment to break up with Lola.
episodes.title: Drug Buddies

episodes.synopsis: While helping Greg move into a seedy bachelor complex, the boys and their dads debate what women want -- and what it means to be a man.
episodes.title: Guy Town

episodes.synopsis: A school sleepover turns messy as Nick dishes on a makeout session and the Shame Wizard works his miserable magic on the whole class.
episodes.title: Dark Side of the Boob

episodes.synopsis: Nick tries to lighten the mood at the sleepover with a new twist on Truth or Dare. The Shame Wizard meets his match. Jessi vows to change her ways.
episodes.title: Smooch or Share

episodes.synopsis: After traveling through a magic portal to puberty headquarters, Nick seeks out a new Hormone Monster and Jessi bonds with the Depression Kitty.
episodes.title: The Department of Puberty

episodes.synopsis: Sappy cards. Stupid clichés. And so much pressure. For Andrew, Nick, Jessi and friends, Valentine's Day is a total freaking minefield.
episodes.title: My Furry Valentine

episodes.synopsis: When a shop class mishap inspires a sexist dress code, Jessi rebels, Missy struggles to keep her alter ego in check, and Andrew gets a wake-up call.
episodes.title: Girls Are Angry Too

episodes.synopsis: Nick is bewitched by his cool new phone. A call from "Pharmacy Boy" turns Matthew into a nervous wreck. Jay finds a Netflix show made just for him.
episodes.title: Cellsea

episodes.synopsis: Cellsea goads Nick into posting a risqué video, Maury urges Matthew to speed things up with Aiden, and Jay feeds Missy ideas for her erotic fiction.
episodes.title: Obsessed

episodes.synopsis: While Nick tags along with the Gloubermans on a wild road trip to Florida, Jay discovers he's been "Home Alone'd" -- and moves in with a new family.
episodes.title: Florida

episodes.synopsis: Connie gives Jessi a crash course in female pleasure, Maury tries to talk Andrew into sending a racy pic, and Nick lashes out at his new housemate.
episodes.title: How To Have An Orgasm

episodes.synopsis: The ghost of Duke Ellington takes Nick and friends on a journey back in time to 1913: the year he lost his virginity and found his true calling.
episodes.title: Duke

episodes.synopsis: As the friends feverishly swap lists of the hottest kids at school, newcomer Ali stokes the flames by announcing she's pansexual.
episodes.title: Rankings

episodes.synopsis: A big standardized test sends everyone into a panic -- except for Jay, who just scored an Adderall prescription.
episodes.title: The ASSes

episodes.synopsis: A provocative school musical unleashes Missy's inner thespian -- and her new Hormone Monstress. The "Queer Eye" Fab Five pay a visit to Coach Steve.
episodes.title: Disclosure the Movie: The Musical!

episodes.synopsis: When a freak storm gives everyone new superpowers, tensions between Andrew, Nick and friends boil over into an epic showdown.
episodes.title: Super Mouth

episodes.synopsis: At sleep-away camp, Jessi befriends her trans cabinmate, and Nick discovers his two best friends have a little too much in common.
episodes.title: The New Me

episodes.synopsis: While Jessi deals with menstrual mayhem, Nick tries to avoid showering with the guys, and Missy gets a makeover from her cousins in Atlanta.
episodes.title: The Hugest Period Ever

episodes.synopsis: On the last night of camp, bowel problems, a talent show and a hookup lead to chaos — and hurt feelings. Back home, Jay and Lola throw a pool party.
episodes.title: Poop Madness

episodes.synopsis: After seeing their eighth grade classmates coupled up, Nick and Andrew make a play for two seventh grade girls. Jessi adjusts to life in the city.
episodes.title: Cafeteria Girls

episodes.synopsis: On a trip to the 9/11 museum, Nick and Andrew sneak off to meet Jessi, Devon teaches Missy about code-switching, and Coach Steve gets a rude surprise.
episodes.title: A Very Special 9/11 Episode

episodes.synopsis: Thirty years in the future, rich but lonely game show host Nick prepares to flee a dying Earth. But first he has to track down the perfect plus-one.
episodes.title: Nick Starr

episodes.synopsis: The kids at Bridgeton Middle explore enthusiastic consent, feminine pleasure, coercion and more in four short films.
episodes.title: Four Stories About Hand Stuff

episodes.synopsis: Wracked with guilt, Andrew tries to keep his urges in check. Matthew's mom ices him out of the church bake-off after reading his texts.
episodes.title: The Funeral

episodes.synopsis: A trippy haunted house hosted by Kappa Kappa Kill forces each of the friends to reckon with their biggest fears.
episodes.title: Horrority House

episodes.synopsis: Forced out of his own body by his smug alter ego, Nick fights back — with help from his friends and the Gratitoad. Matthew comes out to his dad.
episodes.title: What Are You Gonna Do?

episodes.synopsis: To get his mind off Lola, Jay begs his pals to join him in a monthlong challenge. Missy's caught off guard by a new crush.
episodes.title: No Nut November

episodes.synopsis: Eager to get his mojo back, the Shame Wizard drops in on swim class to torment the kids with bodily insecurities.
episodes.title: The Shane Lizard Rises

episodes.synopsis: As Walter the lovebug coaches Nick on matters of the heart, Jessi gets fired up about protesting the school's problematic mascot.
episodes.title: Lovebugs

episodes.synopsis: Unrequited love and jealous rivalries turn the friends into seething beasts. Andrew gets a little too invested in a substitute teacher.
episodes.title: The Green-Eyed Monster

episodes.synopsis: Missy tries to show her cousins she's not a dork, Andrew takes a stand against his dad's turkey tyranny, and Jessi hopes for a Thanksgiving miracle.
episodes.title: Thanksgiving

episodes.synopsis: While Jessi sorts through her feelings for Ali, Nick joins Devon for a boys' night, Andrew shows off his new persona, and Missy starts a rumor online.
episodes.title: Best Friends Make the Best Lovers

episodes.synopsis: Emboldened by their new monsters, Missy and Nick descend into a hate spiral. Meanwhile, Jay puts on a big show to win back Lola.
episodes.title: I F**king Hate You

episodes.synopsis: Classic holiday stories get a naughty makeover in this special episode hosted by puppet versions of Maury and Connie.
episodes.title: A Very Big Mouth Christmas

episodes.synopsis: On a Birch family ski trip, Leah prepares to go all the way with Val, and Andrew hits it off with a fellow ski noob. Matthew helps Jay out of a slump.
episodes.title: Sugarbush

episodes.synopsis: Nick follows Walter to the land of monsters and demands to see the person in charge. A New Year's Eve party inspires a flurry of grand gestures.
episodes.title: Re-New Year's Eve
